31: /**
32:  * A trade in a single-name credit default swap (CDS), resolved for pricing.
33:  * <p>
34:  * This is the resolved form of {@link CdsTrade} and is the primary input to the pricers.
35:  * Applications will typically create a {@code ResolvedCdsTrade} from a {@code CdsTrade}
36:  * using {@link CdsTrade#resolve(ReferenceData)}.
37:  * <p>
38:  * A {@code ResolvedCdsTrade} is bound to data that changes over time, such as holiday calendars.
39:  * If the data changes, such as the addition of a new holiday, the resolved form will not be updated.
40:  * Care must be taken when placing the resolved form in a cache or persistence layer.
41:  */
42: @BeanDefinition
43: public final class ResolvedCdsTrade
44:     implements ResolvedTrade, ImmutableBean, Serializable {
45: 
46:   /**
